Mariska Comins is the Head of Technical Advisory Services at PSG and has worked for the company since 2012. She was previously the PSG Regional Manager for the Western Cape and gained extensive experience in wealth management and insurance products while serving in this role. Comins has achieved a Bachelor of Commerce Honours and was admitted as a Chartered Accountant in 2018. In this episode of Business Talk, Comins talks about retirement annuities and products – including how the economic instability in South Africa is impacting the perception of these retirement vehicles. Comins then explains why retirement vehicles still have a place in a client’s portfolio and unpacks the advantages of investing in a retirement annuity in 2023. She also discusses the process of opening TFIPs for your children or grandchildren and explains why this is a smart idea. Comins concludes by outlining the biggest pitfalls people experience when preparing for retirement – and how to navigate them. You can watch the full interview with Mariska Comins below. <span data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;" class="mce_SELRES_start">﻿</span>